commit.message:
Fix leaks in session_cipher get functions

Fixes #127

Test for endianness during CMake setup

Add an endianness test to the CMake configuration, and use the result of
that test to set a variable that tells the protobuf-c code about the
endianness of the target system.

Fixes #124

Introduce srand_deterministic to match OpenBSD (#120)

* Introduce srand_deterministic to match OpenBSD

Makes explicit deterministic seeding of PRNG obvious.

Fixes #119

Add limits.h include to provide INT_MAX.

Otherwise test build is failing on OpenBSD.
Set library version to 2.3.2 (#110)

Fix warnings (#105)

Initialize pointer in session_record to zero, and make curve tests function a prototype

Fix comments (#104)

* Another magic number removed

* Revert "Another magic number removed"

This reverts commit ac60dfc680deafe5e0e26fc18e6b71b61f647760.

* Update function comments

Comments for a few parameter names are outdated

Explicitly require check 0.9.10+ for unit tests

The tests failed to build with older versions of check due to missing
functions for asserting pointer values. According to the check API docs,
these functions were added in 0.9.10.

Fixes #102
